52class EigenThreadPoolWrapper : public Eigen::ThreadPoolInterface {
53 public:
54 explicit EigenThreadPoolWrapper(thread::ThreadPool* pool) : pool_(pool) {}
55 ~EigenThreadPoolWrapper() override {}
56 void Schedule(std::function<void()> fn) override {
57 auto wrapped = [=]() {
58 // TensorFlow flushes denormals to zero and rounds to nearest, so we do
59 // the same here.
60 port::ScopedFlushDenormal flush;
61 port::ScopedSetRound round(FE_TONEAREST);
62 fn();
63 };
64 pool_->Schedule(std::move(wrapped));
65 }
66 int NumThreads() const override { return pool_->NumThreads(); }
67 int CurrentThreadId() const override { return pool_->CurrentThreadId(); }
68
69 private:
70 thread::ThreadPool* pool_ = nullptr;
71};

73class DeviceSimple : public DeviceBase {
74 public:
75 DeviceSimple() : DeviceBase(Env::Default()) {
76 eigen_worker_threads_.num_threads = port::NumSchedulableCPUs();
77 eigen_worker_threads_.workers = new thread::ThreadPool(
78 Env::Default(), "constant_folding", eigen_worker_threads_.num_threads);
79 eigen_threadpool_wrapper_.reset(
80 new EigenThreadPoolWrapper(eigen_worker_threads_.workers));
81 eigen_device_.reset(new Eigen::ThreadPoolDevice(
82 eigen_threadpool_wrapper_.get(), eigen_worker_threads_.num_threads));
83 set_tensorflow_cpu_worker_threads(&eigen_worker_threads_);
84 set_eigen_cpu_device(eigen_device_.get());
85 }
86 ~DeviceSimple() override {
87 eigen_threadpool_wrapper_.reset();
88 eigen_device_.reset();
89 delete eigen_worker_threads_.workers;
90 }
91 Status MakeTensorFromProto(const TensorProto& tensor_proto,
92 const AllocatorAttributes alloc_attrs,
93 Tensor* tensor) override {
94 Tensor parsed(tensor_proto.dtype());
95 if (!parsed.FromProto(cpu_allocator(), tensor_proto)) {
96 return errors::InvalidArgument("Cannot parse tensor from tensor_proto.");
97 }
98 *tensor = parsed;
99 return Status::OK();
100 }
101 Allocator* GetAllocator(AllocatorAttributes attr) override {
102 return cpu_allocator();
103 }
104
105 private:
106 DeviceBase::CpuWorkerThreads eigen_worker_threads_;
107 std::unique_ptr<Eigen::ThreadPoolInterface> eigen_threadpool_wrapper_;
108 std::unique_ptr<Eigen::ThreadPoolDevice> eigen_device_;
109};

111template <typename T>
112bool AllValuesAre(const TensorProto& proto, const T& value) {
113 Tensor tensor;
114 if (!tensor.FromProto(proto)) {
115 return false;
116 }
117 auto values = tensor.flat<T>();
118 for (int i = 0; i < tensor.NumElements(); ++i) {
119 if (values(i) != value) {
120 return false;
121 }
122 }
123 return true;
124}

126// Add new_input as a control input to node if it does not already depend on it.
127// TODO(rmlarsen): Move the following two utility functions to utils.{h,cc} and
128// clean up code that should be using them.
129bool MaybeAddControlInput(const string& ctrl_input, NodeDef* node,
130 GraphDef* graph, NodeMap* node_map) {
131 bool already_exists = false;
132 for (const string& input : node->input()) {
133 if (input == ctrl_input || AsControlDependency(input) == ctrl_input) {
134 already_exists = true;
135 break;
136 }
137 }
138 if (!already_exists) {
139 const string ctrl_dep =
140 ConstantFolding::AddControlDependency(ctrl_input, graph, node_map);
141 node->add_input(ctrl_dep);
142 node_map->AddOutput(NodeName(ctrl_input), node->name());
143 }
144 return !already_exists;
145}
146
147// Remove old_input as a control input to node.
148bool MaybeRemoveControlInput(const string& old_input, NodeDef* node,
149 GraphDef* graph, NodeMap* node_map) {
150 bool removed_input = false;
151 bool update_node_map = true;
152 const string old_input_ctrl_dep = AsControlDependency(NodeName(old_input));
153 for (int i = 0; i < node->input_size(); ++i) {
154 const string& input = node->input(i);
155 if (old_input_ctrl_dep == input) {
156 if (IsControlInput(input)) {
157 node->mutable_input()->SwapElements(i, node->input_size() - 1);
158 node->mutable_input()->RemoveLast();
159 removed_input = true;
160 } else {
161 // There is a non-control input from the same node.
162 // Don't remove the output from the NodeMap.
163 update_node_map = false;
164 }
165 }
166 }
167 if (update_node_map) {
168 node_map->RemoveOutput(NodeName(old_input), node->name());
169 }
170 return removed_input;
171}

184// static
185string ConstantFolding::AddControlDependency(const string& input_name,
186 GraphDef* graph,
187 NodeMap* node_map) {
188 if (IsControlInput(input_name)) {
189 return input_name;
190 }
191 const NodeDef* node = node_map->GetNode(input_name);
192 if (!IsSwitch(*node)) {
193 return AsControlDependency(*node);
194 } else {
195 // We can't anchor control dependencies directly on the switch node: unlike
196 // other nodes only one of the outputs of the switch node will be generated
197 // when the switch node is executed, and we need to make sure the control
198 // dependency is only triggered when the corresponding output is triggered.
199 // We start by looking for an identity node connected to the output of the
200 // switch node, and use it to anchor the control dependency.
201 auto outputs = node_map->GetOutputs(node->name());
202 for (const NodeDef* output : outputs) {
203 if (IsIdentity(*output)) {
204 if (IsSameInput(node->input(0), input_name)) {
205 return AsControlDependency(*output);
206 }
207 }
208 }
209 // We haven't found an existing node where we can anchor the control
210 // dependency: add a new identity node.
211 int port = 0;
212 string ctrl_dep_name = ParseNodeName(input_name, &port);
213 strings::StrAppend(&ctrl_dep_name, "_", port);
214 ctrl_dep_name = AddPrefixToNodeName(ctrl_dep_name, kConstantFoldingCtrl);
215 const DataType output_type = node->attr().at("T").type();
216
217 NodeDef* added_node = node_map->GetNode(ctrl_dep_name);
218 if (added_node == nullptr) {
219 added_node = graph->add_node();
220 added_node->set_name(ctrl_dep_name);
221 added_node->set_op("Identity");
222 added_node->set_device(node->device());
223
224 (*added_node->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(output_type);
225 *added_node->add_input() = input_name;
226 node_map->AddNode(added_node->name(), added_node);
227 node_map->AddOutput(node->name(), added_node->name());
228 }
229 return AsControlDependency(*added_node);
230 }
231}

233// Puts the given value into the tensor at the given "flat" index.
234static Status PutValueIntoTensor(const int64 value, const DataType& type,
235 const int index, Tensor* tensor) {
236 if (type == DT_INT32) {
237 if (value >= INT_MAX) {
238 return Status(error::INVALID_ARGUMENT, "int32 overflow");
239 }
240 tensor->flat<int32>()(index) = static_cast<int32>(value);
241 } else {
242 tensor->flat<int64>()(index) = value;
243 }
244 return Status::OK();
245}
246
247// Writes the given tensor shape into the given tensor.
248// Op is assumed to be Shape, ShapeN, Size or Rank.
249static Status ConvertShapeToConstant(const string& op, const DataType& type,
250 const PartialTensorShape& shp,
251 Tensor* tensor) {
252 if (op == "Shape" || op == "ShapeN") {
253 *tensor = Tensor(type, TensorShape({shp.dims()}));
254 for (int i = 0; i < shp.dims(); ++i) {
255 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(PutValueIntoTensor(shp.dim_size(i), type, i, tensor));
256 }
257 } else if (op == "Size") {
258 int64 size = 1;
259 for (int i = 0; i < shp.dims(); ++i) {
260 size *= shp.dim_size(i);
261 }
262 *tensor = Tensor(type, TensorShape({}));
263 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(PutValueIntoTensor(size, type, 0, tensor));
264 } else {
265 CHECK_EQ(op, "Rank");
266 *tensor = Tensor(type, TensorShape({}));
267 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(PutValueIntoTensor(shp.dims(), type, 0, tensor));
268 }
269 return Status::OK();
270}

279 StringPiece suffix) const {

281 kConstantFoldingConst);

284bool ConstantFolding::IsReallyConstant(const NodeDef& node) const {
285 if (!IsConstant(node)) {
286 return false;
287 }
288 // If the node is fed it's not constant anymore.
289 return feed_nodes_.find(node.name()) == feed_nodes_.end();
290}

292// Materialize the shapes using constants whenever possible.
293Status ConstantFolding::MaterializeShapes(const GraphProperties& properties) {
294 // We may add some nodes to the graph to encode control dependencies and hold
295 // the materialized shapes: there is no need to process these added nodes, so
296 // only iterate over the nodes of the input graph.
297 const int node_count = graph_->node_size();
298 for (int node_idx = 0; node_idx < node_count; ++node_idx) {
299 NodeDef* node = graph_->mutable_node(node_idx);
300 const string op = node->op();
301 if (op != "Shape" && op != "Size" && op != "Rank" && op != "ShapeN" &&
302 op != "TensorArraySizeV3") {
303 continue;
304 }
305
306 const std::vector<OpInfo::TensorProperties>& output =
307 properties.GetOutputProperties(node->name());
308 const std::vector<OpInfo::TensorProperties>& input =
309 properties.GetInputProperties(node->name());
310 if (input.empty() || output.empty()) {
311 continue;
312 }
313
314 if (op == "Shape" || op == "Size" || op == "Rank") {
315 CHECK_EQ(1, output.size());
316 CHECK_EQ(1, input.size());
317
318 const DataType type = output[0].dtype();
319 CHECK(type == DT_INT32 || type == DT_INT64);
320 const PartialTensorShape shape(input[0].shape());
321
322 if ((op != "Rank" && !shape.IsFullyDefined()) ||
323 (op == "Rank" && shape.unknown_rank())) {
324 continue;
325 }
326
327 Tensor constant_value(type);
328 if (!ConvertShapeToConstant(op, type, shape, &constant_value).ok()) {
329 continue;
330 }
331
332 // Repurpose the existing node to be the constant.
333 // Device placement is preserved.
334 node->set_op("Const");
335 node->clear_attr();
336 (*node->mutable_attr())["dtype"].set_type(type);
337 constant_value.AsProtoTensorContent(
338 (*node->mutable_attr())["value"].mutable_tensor());
339
340 // Turn the data input into a control dependency: this is needed to
341 // ensure that the constant value will only be run in the
342 // cases where the shape/rank/size would have been run in
343 // the original graph.
344 string ctrl_dep =
345 AddControlDependency(node->input(0), graph_, node_map_.get());
346 node->set_input(0, ctrl_dep);
347 node_map_->AddOutput(NodeName(ctrl_dep), node->name());
348
349 // Done with the Shape/Size/Rank node, move to the next node.
350 continue;
351 }
352
353 if (op == "TensorArraySizeV3") {
354 const NodeDef* array = node_map_->GetNode(node->input(0));
355 if (array->attr().count("dynamic_size") != 0 &&
356 array->attr().at("dynamic_size").b()) {
357 continue;
358 }
359 const NodeDef* array_size = node_map_->GetNode(array->input(0));
360 if (IsReallyConstant(*array_size)) {
361 // Don't materialize 0 sizes to avoid triggering incorrect static
362 // checks. A 0 sized array that can't grow isn't useful anyway.
363 const TensorProto& raw_val = array_size->attr().at("value").tensor();
364 if (raw_val.dtype() != DT_INT32) {
365 continue;
366 }
367 Tensor value(raw_val.dtype(), raw_val.tensor_shape());
368 if (!value.FromProto(raw_val)) {
369 continue;
370 }
371 if (value.flat<int32>()(0) == 0) {
372 continue;
373 }
374 node->set_op("Const");
375 *node->mutable_attr() = array_size->attr();
376 node->set_input(0, AsControlDependency(NodeName(node->input(0))));
377 node->set_input(1, AddControlDependency(NodeName(node->input(1)),
378 graph_, node_map_.get()));
379 }
380 continue;
381 }
382
383 // Handle ShapeN materialization case.
384 // It's possible that not all input tensors have known shapes.
385 CHECK_EQ(op, "ShapeN");
386 CHECK_EQ(input.size(), output.size());
387 const NodeDef* const shape_n_node = node;
388 for (int port_idx = 0; port_idx < output.size(); ++port_idx) {
389 const DataType type = output[port_idx].dtype();
390 CHECK(type == DT_INT32 || type == DT_INT64);
391 const PartialTensorShape shape(input[port_idx].shape());
392 if (!shape.IsFullyDefined()) {
393 continue;
394 }
395 Tensor constant_value(type);
396 auto status = ConvertShapeToConstant(op, type, shape, &constant_value);
397 if (!status.ok()) {
398 continue;
399 }
400
401 // Find all nodes consuming this shape and connect them through the new
402 // constant node instead.
403 auto outputs = node_map_->GetOutputs(shape_n_node->name());
404 for (NodeDef* output : outputs) {
405 // Track whether there are any direct edges left between shape_n_node
406 // and this output node after the transformation.
407 bool direct_edges_exist = false;
408 for (int k = 0; k < output->input_size(); ++k) {
409 int port;
410 const string node_name = ParseNodeName(output->input(k), &port);
411 if (node_name == shape_n_node->name() && port == port_idx) {
412 // Create a const node as ShapeN's output if not already.
413 const string const_name = OptimizedNodeName(
414 *shape_n_node, strings::StrCat("-matshapes-", port_idx));
415 if (node_map_->GetNode(const_name) == nullptr) {
416 NodeDef* added_node = graph_->add_node();
417 added_node->set_name(const_name);
418 added_node->set_op("Const");
419 added_node->set_device(shape_n_node->device());
420 node_map_->AddNode(added_node->name(), added_node);
421 (*added_node->mutable_attr())["dtype"].set_type(type);
422 constant_value.AsProtoTensorContent(
423 (*added_node->mutable_attr())["value"].mutable_tensor());
424 // We add a control dependency to the original ShapeN node,
425 // so that the node will only be run if all inputs of the
426 // original ShapeN node are run.
427 string ctrl_dep = AddControlDependency(shape_n_node->name(),
428 graph_, node_map_.get());
429 *added_node->add_input() = ctrl_dep;
430 node_map_->AddOutput(NodeName(ctrl_dep), added_node->name());
431 }
432 *output->mutable_input(k) = const_name;
433 node_map_->AddOutput(const_name, output->name());
434 }
435 if (node_name == shape_n_node->name() && port != port_idx) {
436 direct_edges_exist = true;
437 }
438 }
439 if (!direct_edges_exist) {
440 node_map_->RemoveOutput(node->name(), output->name());
441 }
442 }
443 }
444 }
445
446 return Status::OK();
447}

449namespace {
450bool ShapesEqual(const TensorShapeProto& shape1,
451 const TensorShapeProto& shape2) {
452 if (shape1.unknown_rank() || shape2.unknown_rank()) {
453 return false;
454 }
455 if (shape1.dim_size() != shape2.dim_size()) {
456 return false;
457 }
458 for (int i = 0; i < shape1.dim_size(); ++i) {
459 if (shape1.dim(i).size() != shape2.dim(i).size()) {
460 return false;
461 }
462 if (shape1.dim(i).size() == -1 || shape2.dim(i).size() == -1) {
463 return false;
464 }
465 }
466 return true;
467}
468
469bool ExtractShape(const NodeDef& shape_node, const GraphProperties& properties,
470 BCast::Vec* shape, int64* min_id) {
471 if (shape_node.op() == "Shape") {
472 const std::vector<OpInfo::TensorProperties>& prop1 =
473 properties.GetInputProperties(shape_node.name());
474 if (prop1.size() != 1) {
475 return false;
476 }
477 const TensorShapeProto& shp = prop1[0].shape();
478 if (shp.unknown_rank()) {
479 return false;
480 }
481 for (const auto& dim : shp.dim()) {
482 shape->push_back(dim.size());
483 *min_id = std::min<int64>(*min_id, dim.size());
484 }
485 } else {
486 const TensorProto& raw_val = shape_node.attr().at("value").tensor();
487 if (raw_val.dtype() != DT_INT64 && raw_val.dtype() != DT_INT32) {
488 return false;
489 }
490 Tensor value(raw_val.dtype(), raw_val.tensor_shape());
491 if (!value.FromProto(raw_val)) {
492 return false;
493 }
494 for (int j = 0; j < value.NumElements(); ++j) {
495 if (raw_val.dtype() == DT_INT64) {
496 shape->push_back(value.vec<int64>()(j));
497 } else {
498 shape->push_back(value.vec<int>()(j));
499 }
500 }
501 }
502 return true;
503}

506Status ConstantFolding::MaterializeBroadcastGradientArgs(
507 const NodeDef& node, const GraphProperties& properties) {
508 const NodeDef* shape_node1 = node_map_->GetNode(node.input(0));
509 const NodeDef* shape_node2 = node_map_->GetNode(node.input(1));
510 if (shape_node1 == nullptr ||
511 (shape_node1->op() != "Shape" && !IsReallyConstant(*shape_node1)) ||
512 shape_node2 == nullptr ||
513 (shape_node2->op() != "Shape" && !IsReallyConstant(*shape_node2))) {
514 return Status::OK();
515 }
516
517 // Don't optimize this again if it was already optimized and folded.
518 if (OptimizedNodeExists(node, "-folded-1") ||
519 OptimizedNodeExists(node, "-folded-2")) {
520 return Status::OK();
521 }
522 int64 min_id = 0;
523 BCast::Vec shape1;
524 if (!ExtractShape(*shape_node1, properties, &shape1, &min_id)) {
525 return Status::OK();
526 }
527 BCast::Vec shape2;
528 if (!ExtractShape(*shape_node2, properties, &shape2, &min_id)) {
529 return Status::OK();
530 }
531 // A value of -1 means we don't known anything about the dimension. Replace
532 // the -1 values with unique dimension ids since we don't want two '-1'
533 // dimensions to be considered equal.
534 for (auto& id : shape1) {
535 if (id == -1) {
536 id = --min_id;
537 }
538 }
539 for (auto& id : shape2) {
540 if (id == -1) {
541 id = --min_id;
542 }
543 }
544
545 // Beware: the reduction dimensions computed by the BCast class are valid iff
546 // we assume that two distinct symbolic dimensions can't be equal and a
547 // symbolic dimension can't be equal to 1. This is often but not always true,
548 // so to make this optimization safe we filter out these cases.
549 const int common_dims = std::min(shape1.size(), shape2.size());
550 for (int i = 0; i < common_dims; ++i) {
551 if (shape1[i] >= 0 && shape2[i] >= 0) {
552 continue;
553 }
554 if (shape1[i] != shape2[i]) {
555 // We're either dealing with 2 different symbolic dimensions or a symbolic
556 // and a know dimensions. We can't be sure whether both are equal or not,
557 // so we can't be sure whether we'll be broadcasting or not.
558 return Status::OK();
559 }
560 }
561 // These extra dims could be equal to 1, in which case there is no
562 // broadcasting. It could also be greater than 1, in which case there would
563 // be broadcasting. Since we don't know, we'll just punt.
564 for (int i = common_dims; i < shape1.size(); ++i) {
565 if (shape1[i] < 0) {
566 return Status::OK();
567 }
568 }
569 for (int i = common_dims; i < shape2.size(); ++i) {
570 if (shape2[i] < 0) {
571 return Status::OK();
572 }
573 }
574
575 BCast bcast(shape1, shape2);
576 if (!bcast.IsValid()) {
577 return Status::OK();
578 }
579
580 BCast::Vec reduce_dims[2];
581 reduce_dims[0] = bcast.grad_x_reduce_idx();
582 reduce_dims[1] = bcast.grad_y_reduce_idx();
583
584 const DataType type = node.attr().at("T").type();
585 NodeDef* out[2];
586 for (int j = 0; j < 2; ++j) {
587 int reduction_indices = reduce_dims[j].size();
588 Tensor value(type, TensorShape({reduction_indices}));
589 for (int i = 0; i < reduction_indices; ++i) {
590 if (type == DT_INT32) {
591 value.vec<int32>()(i) = reduce_dims[j][i];
592 } else {
593 value.vec<int64>()(i) = reduce_dims[j][i];
594 }
595 }
596 string const_name =
597 OptimizedNodeName(node, strings::StrCat("-bcastargs-", j));
598 out[j] = node_map_->GetNode(const_name);
599 if (out[j] == nullptr) {
600 out[j] = graph_->add_node();
601 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
602 CreateNodeDef(const_name, TensorValue(&value), out[j]));
603 out[j]->set_device(node.device());
604 node_map_->AddNode(const_name, out[j]);
605 string ctrl_dep =
606 AddControlDependency(node.name(), graph_, node_map_.get());
607 *out[j]->add_input() = ctrl_dep;
608 node_map_->AddOutput(NodeName(ctrl_dep), const_name);
609 }
610 }
611
612 const std::set<NodeDef*> outputs = node_map_->GetOutputs(node.name());
613 for (NodeDef* output : outputs) {
614 for (int k = 0; k < output->input_size(); ++k) {
615 int port;
616 string node_name = ParseNodeName(output->input(k), &port);
617 if (node_name == node.name() && port >= 0 && port < 2 && out[port]) {
618 *output->mutable_input(k) = out[port]->name();
619 node_map_->UpdateInput(output->name(), node_name, out[port]->name());
620 }
621 }
622 }
623
624 return Status::OK();
625}
626
627Status ConstantFolding::MaterializeReductionIndices(
628 NodeDef* node, const GraphProperties& properties) {
629 if (node->input_size() < 2) {
630 return Status::OK();
631 }
632 const NodeDef* indices = node_map_->GetNode(node->input(1));
633 if (!indices || IsReallyConstant(*indices)) {
634 // The reduction indices are already constant, there's nothing to do.
635 return Status::OK();
636 }
637
638 const std::vector<OpInfo::TensorProperties>& input_props =
639 properties.GetInputProperties(node->name());
640 if (input_props.size() != 2) {
641 return Status::OK();
642 }
643 const OpInfo::TensorProperties& input_prop = input_props[0];
644 if (input_prop.shape().unknown_rank()) {
645 // We can't do anything if we don't know the rank of the input.
646 return Status::OK();
647 }
648 const int rank = input_prop.shape().dim_size();
649 if (rank == 0) {
650 // Unexpected graph, don't try to change it.
651 return Status::OK();
652 }
653 const std::vector<OpInfo::TensorProperties>& output_props =
654 properties.GetOutputProperties(node->name());
655 if (output_props.size() != 1) {
656 return Status::OK();
657 }
658 const bool keep_dims =
659 node->attr().count("keep_dims") && node->attr().at("keep_dims").b();
660 const OpInfo::TensorProperties& output_prop = output_props[0];
661 PartialTensorShape output_shape(output_prop.shape());
662 if (output_shape.num_elements() != 1) {
663 bool full_reduction = false;
664 for (const NodeDef* fanout : node_map_->GetOutputs(node->name())) {
665 if (!IsReshape(*fanout) && !keep_dims) {
666 // Depending on how it's setup, a full reduction will generate a tensor
667 // of shape [], [1], [1, 1], [1, 1, ...]. If keep_dims isn't true, we
668 // rely on the existence of a reshape node following the reduction to
669 // ensure that the fanout is fed a scalar of the right shape.
670 return Status::OK();
671 }
672 const std::vector<OpInfo::TensorProperties>& reshape_props =
673 properties.GetOutputProperties(fanout->name());
674 if (reshape_props.size() != 1) {
675 return Status::OK();
676 }
677 const OpInfo::TensorProperties& reshape_prop = reshape_props[0];
678 PartialTensorShape shape(reshape_prop.shape());
679 if (shape.num_elements() != 1) {
680 return Status::OK();
681 } else {
682 full_reduction = true;
683 }
684 }
685 if (!full_reduction) {
686 return Status::OK();
687 }
688 }
689
690 const OpInfo::TensorProperties& reduction_prop = input_props[1];
691 DataType dtype = reduction_prop.dtype();
692 if (dtype != DT_INT32 && dtype != DT_INT64) {
693 return Status::OK();
694 }
695 // We know it's a full reduction. We can generate the set of indices to
696 // reduce.
697 string const_name = OptimizedNodeName(*node, "-reduction_indices");
698 if (node_map_->GetNode(const_name)) {
699 return Status::OK();
700 }
701 NodeDef* reduction_indices = graph_->add_node();
702 Tensor value(dtype, TensorShape({rank}));
703 for (int i = 0; i < rank; ++i) {
704 if (dtype == DT_INT32) {
705 value.vec<int32>()(i) = i;
706 } else {
707 value.vec<int64>()(i) = i;
708 }
709 }
710 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
711 CreateNodeDef(const_name, TensorValue(&value), reduction_indices));
712 reduction_indices->set_device(node->device());
713 string ctrl_dep =
714 AddControlDependency(node->input(1), graph_, node_map_.get());
715 *reduction_indices->add_input() = ctrl_dep;
716 node_map_->AddNode(const_name, reduction_indices);
717 node_map_->AddOutput(NodeName(ctrl_dep), const_name);
718
719 node->set_input(1, reduction_indices->name());
720 node_map_->UpdateInput(node->name(), indices->name(),
721 reduction_indices->name());
722
723 return Status::OK();
724}
725
726Status ConstantFolding::MaterializeConstants(
727 const GraphProperties& properties) {
728 const int node_count = graph_->node_size();
729 for (int i = 0; i < node_count; ++i) {
730 NodeDef& node = *graph_->mutable_node(i);
731 const string& op = node.op();
732 if (op == "BroadcastGradientArgs") {
733 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(MaterializeBroadcastGradientArgs(node, properties));
734 } else if (IsReduction(node)) {
735 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(MaterializeReductionIndices(&node, properties));
736 }
737 }
738 return Status::OK();
739}
740
741bool ConstantFolding::IsFoldable(const NodeDef& node) const {
742 // Folding not applicable to ops with no inputs.
743 if (node.input().empty()) {
744 return false;
745 }
746 // Skips nodes that must be preserved except whitelisted nodes.
747 if (nodes_to_preserve_.find(node.name()) != nodes_to_preserve_.end() &&
748 nodes_whitelist_.find(node.name()) == nodes_whitelist_.end()) {
749 return false;
750 }
751 // Skip control flow nodes, they can't be folded.
752 if (ModifiesFrameInfo(node)) {
753 return false;
754 }
755 // Skip constants, they're already folded
756 if (IsConstant(node)) {
757 return false;
758 }
759
760 // Don't fold stateful ops such as TruncatedNormal.
761 if (!IsFreeOfSideEffect(node)) {
762 return false;
763 }
764
765 // Skips ops that don't benefit from folding.
766 if (IsPlaceholder(node)) {
767 return false;
768 }
769 const string& op = node.op();
770 if (op.find("Save") != string::npos || op.find("Restore") != string::npos ||
771 op.find("Reader") != string::npos) {
772 return false;
773 }
774 if (op.find("Quantized") != string::npos || op.find("Sparse") == 0) {
775 return false;
776 }
777
778 const OpDef* op_def = nullptr;
779 Status status = OpRegistry::Global()->LookUpOpDef(node.op(), &op_def);
780 if (!status.ok()) {
781 return false;
782 }
783 // Don't fold ops without outputs.
784 if (op_def->output_arg_size() == 0) {
785 return false;
786 }
787
788 // No need to (and don't) fold nodes that have no outgoing edges except
789 // whitelisted nodes. Such nodes could be introduced by an earlier constant
790 // folding pass and are preserved in case users want to fetch their values;
791 // re-processing them would lead to an error of adding a duplicated node
792 // to graph.
793 auto outputs = node_map_->GetOutputs(node.name());
794 if (outputs.empty() &&
795 nodes_whitelist_.find(node.name()) == nodes_whitelist_.end()) {
796 return false;
797 }
798
799 // We can only fold nodes if all their inputs are known statically, except in
800 // the case of a merge node that propagate the first inputs that becomes
801 // available, and therefore only requires a single constant input to be
802 // foldable.
803 bool merge_has_constant_input = false;
804 const bool is_merge = IsMerge(node);
805 for (const auto& input : node.input()) {
806 if (IsControlInput(input)) {
807 continue;
808 }
809 const NodeDef* input_node = node_map_->GetNode(input);
810 if (!input_node) {
811 return false;
812 }
813 bool is_const = IsReallyConstant(*input_node);
814 if (is_const) {
815 // Don't fold strings constants for now since this causes problems with
816 // checkpointing.
817 if (input_node->attr().at("dtype").type() == DT_STRING) {
818 return false;
819 }
820 // Special case: If a Merge node has at least one constant input that
821 // does not depend on a control input, we can fold it.
822 merge_has_constant_input |= !HasControlInputs(*input_node);
823 } else if (!is_merge) {
824 return false;
825 }
826 }
827 return !is_merge || merge_has_constant_input;
828}

832#define SET_TENSOR_VAL_CASE(DTYPE, TYPE, NAME) \
833 case DTYPE: \
834 t->add_##NAME##_val(static_cast<TYPE>(value)); \
835 break;
836
837Status CreateConstantTensorAttrValue(DataType type, double value,
838 const TensorShapeProto& shape,
839 AttrValue* attr_tensor) {
840 TensorProto* t = attr_tensor->mutable_tensor();
841 t->set_dtype(type);
842 *t->mutable_tensor_shape() = shape;
843 switch (type) {
844 case DT_HALF:
845 t->add_half_val(static_cast<Eigen::half>(value).x);
846 break;
847 case DT_BFLOAT16:
848 t->add_half_val(static_cast<bfloat16>(value).value);
849 break;
850 SET_TENSOR_VAL_CASE(DT_FLOAT, float, float);
851 SET_TENSOR_VAL_CASE(DT_DOUBLE, double, double);
852 SET_TENSOR_VAL_CASE(DT_INT64, int64, int64);
853 SET_TENSOR_VAL_CASE(DT_UINT64, int64, int64);
854 SET_TENSOR_VAL_CASE(DT_INT32, int32, int);
855 SET_TENSOR_VAL_CASE(DT_UINT32, int32, int);
856 SET_TENSOR_VAL_CASE(DT_INT16, int32, int);
857 SET_TENSOR_VAL_CASE(DT_UINT16, int32, int);
858 SET_TENSOR_VAL_CASE(DT_INT8, int32, int);
859 SET_TENSOR_VAL_CASE(DT_UINT8, int32, int);
860 SET_TENSOR_VAL_CASE(DT_BOOL, bool, bool);
861 default:
862 return errors::InvalidArgument("Unsupported type: ", type);
863 }
864 return Status::OK();
865}

870// static
871Status ConstantFolding::CreateNodeDef(const string& name,
872 const TensorValue& tensor,
873 NodeDef* node) {
874 node->set_name(name);
875 node->set_op("Const");
876
877 AttrValue attr_type;
878 attr_type.set_type(tensor->dtype());
879 node->mutable_attr()->insert({"dtype", attr_type});
880
881 AttrValue attr_tensor;
882 TensorProto* t = attr_tensor.mutable_tensor();
883 bool optimized = false;
884 size_t encoded_size;
885 // Use the packed representation whenever possible to avoid generating large
886 // graphdefs. Moreover, avoid repeating the last values if they're equal.
887 if (tensor->NumElements() > 4) {
888#define POPULATE_TENSOR_PROTO(tensor, t, TYPE, NAME) \
889 { \
890 const TYPE* val_ptr = tensor->flat<TYPE>().data(); \
891 TYPE last = *val_ptr; \
892 int64 last_index = 0; \
893 for (int64 i = 0; i < tensor->NumElements(); ++i) { \
894 TYPE cur = *val_ptr++; \
895 if (cur != last) { \
896 last = cur; \
897 last_index = i; \
898 } \
899 } \
900 if (last_index < kint32max) { \
901 optimized = true; \
902 encoded_size = (last_index + 1) * sizeof(NAME); \
903 t->mutable_##NAME##_val()->Reserve(last_index + 1); \
904 t->mutable_##NAME##_val()->AddNAlreadyReserved(last_index + 1); \
905 val_ptr = tensor->flat<TYPE>().data(); \
906 for (int64 i = 0; i <= last_index; ++i) { \
907 t->set_##NAME##_val(i, *val_ptr++); \
908 } \
909 } \
910 } \
911 break
912
913 switch (tensor->dtype()) {
914 case DT_FLOAT:
915 POPULATE_TENSOR_PROTO(tensor, t, float, float);
916 case DT_DOUBLE:
917 POPULATE_TENSOR_PROTO(tensor, t, double, double);
918 case DT_INT64:
919 POPULATE_TENSOR_PROTO(tensor, t, int64, int64);
920 case DT_UINT64:
921 POPULATE_TENSOR_PROTO(tensor, t, uint64, int64);
922 case DT_INT32:
923 POPULATE_TENSOR_PROTO(tensor, t, int32, int);
924 case DT_UINT32:
925 POPULATE_TENSOR_PROTO(tensor, t, uint32, int);
926 case DT_INT16:
927 POPULATE_TENSOR_PROTO(tensor, t, int16, int);
928 case DT_UINT16:
929 POPULATE_TENSOR_PROTO(tensor, t, uint16, int);
930 case DT_INT8:
931 POPULATE_TENSOR_PROTO(tensor, t, int8, int);
932 case DT_UINT8:
933 POPULATE_TENSOR_PROTO(tensor, t, uint8, int);
934 case DT_BOOL:
935 POPULATE_TENSOR_PROTO(tensor, t, bool, bool);
936 default:
937 /* Do nothing. */
938 break;
939 }
940 }
941 if (optimized) {
942 // Also specify type and shape.
943 t->set_dtype(tensor->dtype());
944 tensor->shape().AsProto(t->mutable_tensor_shape());
945 } else {
946 tensor->AsProtoTensorContent(t);
947 encoded_size = t->tensor_content().size();
948 }
949 node->mutable_attr()->insert({"value", attr_tensor});
950
951 if (encoded_size < 10 * 1024 * 1024) {
952 return Status::OK();
953 }
954 return errors::InvalidArgument(
955 strings::StrCat("Can't fold ", name, ", its size would be too large"));
956}
957
958Status ConstantFolding::EvaluateNode(const NodeDef& node,
959 const TensorVector& inputs,
960 TensorVector* output) const {
961 Status status;
962 auto op_kernel =
963 CreateOpKernel("CPU", cpu_device_, cpu_device_->GetAllocator({}), node,
964 TF_GRAPH_DEF_VERSION, &status);
965 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(status);
966 OpKernelContext::Params params;
967 params.device = cpu_device_;
968 params.frame_iter = FrameAndIter(0, 0);
969 params.inputs = &inputs;
970 params.op_kernel = op_kernel.get();
971 params.resource_manager = resource_mgr_.get();
972
973 gtl::InlinedVector<AllocatorAttributes, 4> output_attrs;
974 const int num_outputs = op_kernel->num_outputs();
975 for (int i = 0; i < num_outputs; i++) {
976 AllocatorAttributes attr;
977 attr.set_on_host(true);
978 output_attrs.push_back(attr);
979 }
980 params.output_attr_array = output_attrs.data();
981
982 OpKernelContext op_context(&params);
983 op_kernel->Compute(&op_context);
984 for (int i = 0; i < num_outputs; i++) {
985 output->push_back(op_context.release_output(i));
986 }
987 return op_context.status();
988}
989
990Status ConstantFolding::EvaluateOneFoldable(const NodeDef& node,
991 std::vector<NodeDef>* outputs) {
992 TensorVector inputs;
993 TensorVector output_tensors;
994 auto inputs_cleanup = gtl::MakeCleanup([&inputs, &output_tensors] {
995 for (const auto& input : inputs) {
996 delete input.tensor;
997 }
998 for (const auto& output : output_tensors) {
999 if (output.tensor) {
1000 delete output.tensor;
1001 }
1002 }
1003 });
1004
1005 for (const auto& input : node.input()) {
1006 int port = 0;
1007 ParseNodeName(input, &port);
1008 if (port < 0) {
1009 // Control dependency
1010 break;
1011 }
1012 const NodeDef* input_node = node_map_->GetNode(input);
1013 if (!IsReallyConstant(*input_node)) {
1014 return Status(error::INVALID_ARGUMENT,
1015 strings::StrCat("Can't fold ", node.name(), ", its ", input,
1016 " isn't constant"));
1017 }
1018 const TensorProto& raw_val = input_node->attr().at("value").tensor();
1019 Tensor* value = new Tensor(raw_val.dtype(), raw_val.tensor_shape());
1020 CHECK(value->FromProto(raw_val));
1021 inputs.emplace_back(value);
1022 }
1023
1024 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(EvaluateNode(node, inputs, &output_tensors));
1025 if (output_tensors.empty()) {
1026 return Status(error::INVALID_ARGUMENT, "Expected at least one output.");
1027 }
1028
1029 outputs->resize(output_tensors.size());
1030 for (size_t i = 0; i < output_tensors.size(); i++) {
1031 string node_name = OptimizedNodeName(node, "-folded");
1032 if (output_tensors.size() > 1) {
1033 node_name = strings::StrCat(node_name, "-", i);
1034 }
1035 if (output_tensors[i].tensor) {
1036 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
1037 CreateNodeDef(node_name, output_tensors[i], &outputs->at(i)));
1038 } else {
1039 // Create an empty NodeDef to identify dead outputs (e.g. the output of a
1040 // switch that's not selected by the switch predicate).
1041 outputs->at(i) = NodeDef();
1042 }
1043 }
1044 return Status::OK();
1045}
1046
1047Status ConstantFolding::FoldNode(NodeDef* node, GraphDef* output_graph) {
1048 if (IsMerge(*node)) {
1049 // Merge nodes are special, in the sense that they execute as soon as one of
1050 // their input is ready. We can therefore fold a merge node iff it has at
1051 // least one constant input without control dependency.
1052 // We still need to ensure that the nodes in the fanin of the merge node are
1053 // scheduled. We'll therefore add a control dependency from the merge node
1054 // to the folded constant. We end up with:
1055 // * the merge node and its inputs are preserved as is
1056 // * a new constant node C1, driven by the merge node through a control
1057 // dependency, initialized to the value of the folded input
1058 // * a new constant node C2, driven by the merge node through a control
1059 // dependency, initialized to the index of the folded input
1060 // * the fanout of the merge nodes is rewired to be driven by either C1 or
1061 // C2.
1062 for (int input_index = 0; input_index < node->input_size(); ++input_index) {
1063 const auto& input = node->input(input_index);
1064 if (IsControlInput(input)) {
1065 // Try the next input.
1066 continue;
1067 }
1068 NodeDef* input_node = node_map_->GetNode(input);
1069 if (!IsReallyConstant(*input_node)) {
1070 continue;
1071 }
1072 bool valid_input = true;
1073 for (const string& fanin_of_input : input_node->input()) {
1074 if (IsControlInput(fanin_of_input)) {
1075 valid_input = false;
1076 break;
1077 }
1078 }
1079 if (!valid_input) {
1080 // Try the next input
1081 continue;
1082 }
1083
1084 string const_out_name = OptimizedNodeName(*node, "_const");
1085 string const_index_name = OptimizedNodeName(*node, "_index");
1086 if (node_map_->GetNode(const_out_name) ||
1087 node_map_->GetNode(const_index_name)) {
1088 // Intended name already exists.
1089 return errors::AlreadyExists(
1090 strings::StrCat(const_out_name, " or ", const_index_name,
1091 " already present in the graph"));
1092 }
1093
1094 NodeDef* const_out = output_graph->add_node();
1095 *const_out = *input_node;
1096 const_out->set_name(const_out_name);
1097 const_out->set_device(node->device());
1098 *const_out->add_input() = AsControlDependency(*node);
1099 node_map_->AddNode(const_out->name(), const_out);
1100 node_map_->AddOutput(node->name(), const_out->name());
1101
1102 NodeDef* const_index = output_graph->add_node();
1103 const_index->set_op("Const");
1104 Tensor index(DT_INT32, TensorShape({}));
1105 index.flat<int32>()(0) = input_index;
1106 (*const_index->mutable_attr())["dtype"].set_type(DT_INT32);
1107 index.AsProtoTensorContent(
1108 (*const_index->mutable_attr())["value"].mutable_tensor());
1109 const_index->set_name(const_index_name);
1110 const_index->set_device(node->device());
1111 *const_index->add_input() = AsControlDependency(*node);
1112 node_map_->AddNode(const_index->name(), const_index);
1113 node_map_->AddOutput(node->name(), const_index->name());
1114
1115 auto outputs = node_map_->GetOutputs(node->name());
1116 for (NodeDef* output : outputs) {
1117 for (int i = 0; i < output->input_size(); i++) {
1118 int port;
1119 string node_name = ParseNodeName(output->input(i), &port);
1120 if (node_name == node->name()) {
1121 if (port == 0) {
1122 *output->mutable_input(i) = const_out->name();
1123 node_map_->AddOutput(const_out->name(), output->name());
1124 } else if (port == 1) {
1125 *output->mutable_input(i) = const_index->name();
1126 node_map_->AddOutput(const_index->name(), output->name());
1127 } else {
1128 // This is a control dependency (or an invalid edge since the
1129 // merge node has only 2 inputs): preserve them.
1130 }
1131 }
1132 }
1133 }
1134 return Status::OK();
1135 }
1136 return Status::OK();
1137 }
1138
1139 std::vector<NodeDef> const_nodes;
1140 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(EvaluateOneFoldable(*node, &const_nodes));
1141 NodeDef* constant_output = nullptr;
1142 for (int i = 0; i < const_nodes.size(); i++) {
1143 NodeDef* const_node = &const_nodes[i];
1144 if (const_node->name().empty()) {
1145 // Dead output: we can't create a constant to encode its value, so we'll
1146 // just skip it. We'll preserve the edges that originate from that
1147 // output below to preserve the overall behavior of the graph wrt dead
1148 // edges.
1149 continue;
1150 }
1151
1152 // Forward control dependencies.
1153 for (const auto& input : node->input()) {
1154 if (IsControlInput(input) &&
1155 std::find(const_node->input().begin(), const_node->input().end(),
1156 input) == const_node->input().end()) {
1157 *const_node->add_input() = input;
1158 } else {
1159 NodeDef* input_node = node_map_->GetNode(input);
1160 for (const auto& fanin_of_input : input_node->input()) {
1161 if (IsControlInput(fanin_of_input) &&
1162 std::find(const_node->input().begin(), const_node->input().end(),
1163 fanin_of_input) == const_node->input().end()) {
1164 *const_node->add_input() = fanin_of_input;
1165 }
1166 }
1167 }
1168 }
1169
1170 // We rewrite the existing node if it only has a single output, and
1171 // create new nodes otherwise.
1172 if (const_nodes.size() == 1) {
1173 node->set_op("Const");
1174 // Note we need to clear the inputs in NodeMap before we clear the inputs
1175 // in the node, otherwise NodeMap would see empty inputs and effectively
1176 // does nothing.
1177 node_map_->RemoveInputs(node->name());
1178 node->clear_input();
1179 *node->mutable_input() = const_node->input();
1180 for (const auto& input : node->input()) {
1181 node_map_->AddOutput(NodeName(input), node->name());
1182 }
1183 *node->mutable_attr() = const_node->attr();
1184 break;
1185 } else {
1186 if (node_map_->GetNode(const_node->name())) {
1187 // Intended name already exists.
1188 return errors::AlreadyExists(strings::StrCat(
1189 const_node->name(), " already present in the graph"));
1190 }
1191 NodeDef* added_node = output_graph->add_node();
1192 *added_node = *const_node;
1193 added_node->set_device(node->device());
1194 node_map_->AddNode(added_node->name(), added_node);
1195 for (const auto& input : added_node->input()) {
1196 node_map_->AddOutput(NodeName(input), added_node->name());
1197 }
1198 // All the constant nodes encoding output values have the same control
1199 // dependencies (since these are the control dependencies of the node
1200 // we're trying to fold). Record one such constant node.
1201 constant_output = added_node;
1202 }
1203 }
1204
1205 if (const_nodes.size() > 1) {
1206 auto outputs = node_map_->GetOutputs(node->name());
1207 for (NodeDef* output : outputs) {
1208 for (int i = 0; i < output->input_size(); i++) {
1209 int port;
1210 string node_name = ParseNodeName(output->input(i), &port);
1211 if (node_name == node->name()) {
1212 if (port < 0) {
1213 // Propagate control dependencies if possible. If not, we'll just
1214 // preserve the existing control dependencies.
1215 if (constant_output != nullptr) {
1216 node_map_->UpdateInput(node_name, NodeName(output->input(i)),
1217 constant_output->name());
1218 *output->mutable_input(i) = AsControlDependency(*constant_output);
1219 }
1220 } else if (port < const_nodes.size() &&
1221 !const_nodes[port].name().empty()) {
1222 // Replace alive outputs with the corresponding constant.
1223 node_map_->UpdateInput(output->name(), NodeName(output->input(i)),
1224 const_nodes[port].name());
1225 *output->mutable_input(i) = const_nodes[port].name();
1226 } else {
1227 // Leave this edge alone.
1228 VLOG(1) << "Preserving edge from " << node->name() << ":" << port
1229 << "[" << node->op() << "] to " << output->name() << ":"
1230 << i << "[" << output->op() << "]";
1231 }
1232 }
1233 }
1234 }
1235 outputs = node_map_->GetOutputs(node->name());
1236 if (outputs.empty() && has_fetch_ &&
1237 nodes_to_preserve_.find(node->name()) == nodes_to_preserve_.end()) {
1238 node_map_->RemoveInputs(node->name());
1239 node->clear_input();
1240 }
1241 }
1242 return Status::OK();
1243}
1244
1245Status ConstantFolding::FoldGraph(GraphDef* output) {
1246 std::unordered_set<string> processed_nodes;
1247 std::deque<NodeDef*> queue;
1248 for (int i = 0; i < graph_->node_size(); i++) {
1249 if (IsFoldable(graph_->node(i))) {
1250 queue.push_back(graph_->mutable_node(i));
1251 }
1252 }
1253 while (!queue.empty()) {
1254 NodeDef* node = queue.front();
1255 queue.pop_front();
1256 if (processed_nodes.count(node->name())) {
1257 continue;
1258 }
1259 // We need to record a copy of output nodes before FoldNode() modifies it.
1260 // We also need to ensure that the fanout is sorted deterministically.
1261 const std::set<NodeDef*>& outputs = node_map_->GetOutputs(node->name());
1262 std::vector<NodeDef*> fanout(outputs.begin(), outputs.end());
1263 std::sort(fanout.begin(), fanout.end(),
1264 [](const NodeDef* n1, const NodeDef* n2) {
1265 return n1->name() < n2->name();
1266 });
1267
1268 Status s = FoldNode(node, output);
1269 processed_nodes.insert(node->name());
1270 if (!s.ok()) {
1271 VLOG(1) << "Failed to fold node " << node->DebugString()
1272 << "\nError message: " << s;
1273 } else {
1274 for (auto& output : fanout) {
1275 if (IsFoldable(*output)) {
1276 queue.push_back(output);
1277 }
1278 }
1279 }
1280 }
1281
1282 // Delete the newly created nodes that don't feed anything.
1283 int last = output->node_size() - 1;
1284 for (int i = output->node_size() - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
1285 const NodeDef& node = output->node(i);
1286 auto fanout = node_map_->GetOutputs(node.name());
1287 if (fanout.empty()) {
1288 output->mutable_node()->SwapElements(i, last);
1289 last--;
1290 }
1291 }
1292 output->mutable_node()->DeleteSubrange(last + 1,
1293 output->node_size() - last - 1);
1294
1295 for (const auto& node : graph_->node()) {
1296 // If no fetch nodes is provided, we conservatively
1297 // keep all nodes in the original graph in case users need to fetch
1298 // their values.
1299 auto fanout = node_map_->GetOutputs(node.name());
1300 if (!fanout.empty() || !has_fetch_ ||
1301 nodes_to_preserve_.find(node.name()) != nodes_to_preserve_.end()) {
1302 auto added_node = output->add_node();
1303 *added_node = node;
1304 }
1305 }
1306 return Status::OK();
1307}
1308
1309// Returns true iff this reduction can be reduced to an identity (i.e if the set
1310// of dimensions to reduce along is empty). This happens often in the gradient
1311// graphs.
1312bool ConstantFolding::IsSimplifiableReduction(const NodeDef& node) const {
1313 if (IsReduction(node)) {
1314 CHECK_LE(2, node.input_size());
1315 const NodeDef* reductions_indices = node_map_->GetNode(node.input(1));
1316 if (IsReallyConstant(*reductions_indices)) {
1317 TensorVector output;
1318 Status s = EvaluateNode(*reductions_indices, TensorVector(), &output);
1319 if (!s.ok()) {
1320 return false;
1321 }
1322 CHECK_EQ(1, output.size());
1323 int output_size = output[0]->NumElements();
1324 delete output[0].tensor;
1325 if (output_size == 0) {
1326 return true;
1327 }
1328 }
1329 }
1330 return false;
1331}
1332
1333bool ConstantFolding::IsSimplifiableReshape(
1334 const NodeDef& node, const GraphProperties& properties) const {
1335 if (!IsReshape(node)) {
1336 return false;
1337 }
1338 CHECK_LE(2, node.input_size());
1339 const NodeDef* new_shape = node_map_->GetNode(node.input(1));
1340 if (!IsReallyConstant(*new_shape)) {
1341 return false;
1342 }
1343 TensorVector outputs;
1344 auto outputs_cleanup = gtl::MakeCleanup([&outputs] {
1345 for (const auto& output : outputs) {
1346 delete output.tensor;
1347 }
1348 });
1349
1350 Status s = EvaluateNode(*new_shape, TensorVector(), &outputs);
1351 if (!s.ok()) {
1352 return false;
1353 }
1354 CHECK_EQ(1, outputs.size());
1355
1356 const std::vector<OpInfo::TensorProperties>& props =
1357 properties.GetInputProperties(node.name());
1358 if (props.empty()) {
1359 return false;
1360 }
1361 const OpInfo::TensorProperties& prop = props[0];
1362 if (prop.dtype() == DT_INVALID) {
1363 return false;
1364 }
1365 const PartialTensorShape shape(prop.shape());
1366 if (!shape.IsFullyDefined()) {
1367 return false;
1368 }
1369
1370 PartialTensorShape new_dims;
1371 if (outputs[0]->dtype() == DT_INT32) {
1372 std::vector<int32> shp;
1373 for (int i = 0; i < outputs[0]->NumElements(); ++i) {
1374 int32 dim = outputs[0]->flat<int32>()(i);
1375 shp.push_back(dim);
1376 }
1377 TF_CHECK_OK(TensorShapeUtils::MakeShape(shp, &new_dims));
1378 } else {
1379 std::vector<int64> shp;
1380 for (int i = 0; i < outputs[0]->NumElements(); ++i) {
1381 int64 dim = outputs[0]->flat<int64>()(i);
1382 shp.push_back(dim);
1383 }
1384 TF_CHECK_OK(TensorShapeUtils::MakeShape(shp, &new_dims));
1385 }
1386
1387 return shape.IsCompatibleWith(new_dims);
1388}
1389
1390#define IS_VALUE_CASE(DTYPE, VALUE) \
1391 case DTYPE: \
1392 return AllValuesAre<EnumToDataType<DTYPE>::Type>( \
1393 node.attr().at("value").tensor(), EnumToDataType<DTYPE>::Type(VALUE))
1394
1395#define IS_ONES_CASE(TYPE) IS_VALUE_CASE(TYPE, 1)
1396#define IS_ZEROS_CASE(TYPE) IS_VALUE_CASE(TYPE, 0)
1397
1398bool ConstantFolding::IsOnes(const NodeDef& node) const {
1399 if (feed_nodes_.find(node.name()) != feed_nodes_.end()) {
1400 return false;
1401 }
1402 if (node.op() == "OnesLike") {
1403 return true;
1404 }
1405 if (node.op() == "Fill") {
1406 NodeDef* values = node_map_->GetNode(NodeName(node.input(1)));
1407 return values != nullptr && IsOnes(*values);
1408 }
1409 if (node.op() != "Const") {
1410 return false;
1411 }
1412 const auto dtype = node.attr().at("dtype").type();
1413 switch (dtype) {
1414 IS_ONES_CASE(DT_HALF);
1415 IS_ONES_CASE(DT_BFLOAT16);
1416 IS_ONES_CASE(DT_FLOAT);
1417 IS_ONES_CASE(DT_DOUBLE);
1418 IS_ONES_CASE(DT_COMPLEX64);
1419 IS_ONES_CASE(DT_COMPLEX128);
1420 IS_ONES_CASE(DT_UINT8);
1421 IS_ONES_CASE(DT_INT8);
1422 IS_ONES_CASE(DT_UINT16);
1423 IS_ONES_CASE(DT_INT16);
1424 IS_ONES_CASE(DT_INT32);
1425 IS_ONES_CASE(DT_INT64);
1426 default:
1427 VLOG(1) << "Unsupported type " << DataTypeString(dtype);
1428 return false;
1429 }
1430 return false;
1431}
1432
1433bool ConstantFolding::IsZeros(const NodeDef& node) const {
1434 if (feed_nodes_.find(node.name()) != feed_nodes_.end()) {
1435 return false;
1436 }
1437 if (node.op() == "ZerosLike") {
1438 return true;
1439 }
1440 if (node.op() == "Fill") {
1441 NodeDef* values = node_map_->GetNode(NodeName(node.input(1)));
1442 return values != nullptr && IsZeros(*values);
1443 }
1444 if (!IsConstant(node)) {
1445 return false;
1446 }
1447 const auto dtype = node.attr().at("dtype").type();
1448 switch (dtype) {
1449 IS_ZEROS_CASE(DT_HALF);
1450 IS_ZEROS_CASE(DT_BFLOAT16);
1451 IS_ZEROS_CASE(DT_FLOAT);
1452 IS_ZEROS_CASE(DT_DOUBLE);
1453 IS_ZEROS_CASE(DT_COMPLEX64);
1454 IS_ZEROS_CASE(DT_COMPLEX128);
1455 IS_ZEROS_CASE(DT_UINT8);
1456 IS_ZEROS_CASE(DT_INT8);
1457 IS_ZEROS_CASE(DT_UINT16);
1458 IS_ZEROS_CASE(DT_INT16);
1459 IS_ZEROS_CASE(DT_INT32);
1460 IS_ZEROS_CASE(DT_INT64);
1461 default:
1462 VLOG(1) << "Unsupported type " << DataTypeString(dtype);
1463 return false;
1464 }
1465 return false;
1466}
1467
1468void ConstantFolding::ReplaceOperationWithIdentity(int input_to_forward,
1469 NodeDef* node,
1470 GraphDef* graph) {
1471 node->set_op("Identity");
1472 DataType dtype = node->attr().at("T").type();
1473 node->clear_attr();
1474 (*node->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(dtype);
1475
1476 // Propagate the designated input through the identity.
1477 node->mutable_input()->SwapElements(0, input_to_forward);
1478 // Add all other inputs as control dependencies.
1479 for (int i = 1; i < node->input_size(); ++i) {
1480 if (IsControlInput(node->input(i))) {
1481 break;
1482 }
1483 const string ctrl_dep =
1484 AddControlDependency(node->input(i), graph, node_map_.get());
1485 node_map_->UpdateInput(node->name(), node->input(i), ctrl_dep);
1486 node->set_input(i, ctrl_dep);
1487 }
1488 graph_modified_ = true;
1489}
1490
1491void ConstantFolding::ReplaceOperationWithSnapshot(int input_to_forward,
1492 NodeDef* node,
1493 GraphDef* graph) {
1494 node->set_op("Snapshot");
1495 DataType dtype = node->attr().at("T").type();
1496 node->clear_attr();
1497 (*node->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(dtype);
1498
1499 // Propagate the designated input through the Snapshot.
1500 node->mutable_input()->SwapElements(0, input_to_forward);
1501 // Add all other inputs as control dependencies.
1502 for (int i = 1; i < node->input_size(); ++i) {
1503 if (IsControlInput(node->input(i))) {
1504 break;
1505 }
1506 const string ctrl_dep =
1507 AddControlDependency(node->input(i), graph, node_map_.get());
1508 node_map_->UpdateInput(node->name(), node->input(i), ctrl_dep);
1509 node->set_input(i, ctrl_dep);
1510 }
1511 graph_modified_ = true;
1512}

1514void ConstantFolding::ReplaceDivisionOfOnesByReciprocal(NodeDef* node,
1515 GraphDef* graph) {
1516 node->set_op("Reciprocal");
1517 node->mutable_input()->SwapElements(0, 1);
1518 const string ctrl_dep =
1519 AddControlDependency(node->input(1), graph, node_map_.get());
1520 node_map_->UpdateInput(node->name(), node->input(1), ctrl_dep);
1521 node->set_input(1, ctrl_dep);
1522 graph_modified_ = true;

1525void ConstantFolding::ReplaceSubtractionFromZeroByNegation(NodeDef* node,
