1528 node->mutable_input()->SwapElements(0, 1);
1529 const string ctrl_dep =
1530 AddControlDependency(node->input(1), graph, node_map_.get());
1531 node_map_->UpdateInput(node->name(), node->input(1), ctrl_dep);
1532 node->set_input(1, ctrl_dep);
1533 graph_modified_ = true;
1534}
1535
1536Status ConstantFolding::ReplaceOperationWithConstant(
1537 double value, const AttrValue& dtype_attr, const TensorShapeProto& shape,
1538 NodeDef* node, GraphDef* graph) {
1539 AttrValue tensor_attr;
1540 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(CreateConstantTensorAttrValue(dtype_attr.type(), value,
1541 shape, &tensor_attr));
1542 node->clear_attr();
1543 node->mutable_attr()->insert({"dtype", dtype_attr});
1544 node->mutable_attr()->insert({"value", tensor_attr});
1545 node->set_op("Const");
1546 // Convert all inputs to control dependencies.
1547 for (int i = 0; i < node->input_size(); ++i) {
1548 if (IsControlInput(node->input(i))) {
1549 break;
1550 }
1551 const string ctrl_dep =
1552 AddControlDependency(node->input(i), graph, node_map_.get());
1553 node_map_->UpdateInput(node->name(), node->input(i), ctrl_dep);
1554 node->set_input(i, ctrl_dep);
1555 }
1556 graph_modified_ = true;
1557 return Status::OK();
1558}
1559
1560Status ConstantFolding::SimplifyGraph(GraphDef* optimized_graph,
1561 GraphProperties* properties,
1562 bool use_shape_info) {
1563 const bool is_aggressive = opt_level_ == RewriterConfig::AGGRESSIVE;
1564 for (int i = 0; i < optimized_graph->node_size(); ++i) {
1565 NodeDef* node = optimized_graph->mutable_node(i);
1566
1567 if (IsSplit(*node) && node->attr().at("num_split").i() == 1) {
1568 ReplaceOperationWithIdentity(1, node, optimized_graph);
1569 continue;
1570 }
1571
1572 if (IsSplitV(*node) && node->attr().at("num_split").i() == 1) {
1573 ReplaceOperationWithIdentity(0, node, optimized_graph);
1574 continue;
1575 }
1576
1577 // Remove Shuffle or Reverse op over scalar values.
1578 if (use_shape_info &&
1579 !properties->GetInputProperties(node->name()).empty() &&
1580 (IsShuffle(*node) || IsReverse(*node) || IsTranspose(*node))) {
1581 const auto& shape =
1582 properties->GetInputProperties(node->name())[0].shape();
1583 // The node is replaceable iff
1584 // unknown_rank == false && (dim_size == 0 || all dims have size 1)
1585 bool replaceable = !shape.unknown_rank();
1586 for (int j = 0; replaceable && j < shape.dim_size(); ++j) {
1587 replaceable &= shape.dim(j).size() == 1;
1588 }
1589 if (replaceable) {
1590 ReplaceOperationWithIdentity(0, node, optimized_graph);
1591 continue;
1592 }
1593 }
1594
1595 if (use_shape_info && IsSlice(*node) &&
1596 properties->GetInputProperties(node->name()).size() == 3) {
1597 const auto& input = properties->GetInputProperties(node->name())[0];
1598 const auto& b = properties->GetInputProperties(node->name())[1];
1599 const auto& s = properties->GetInputProperties(node->name())[2];
1600 if (TensorShape::IsValid(b.shape()) && b.has_value() &&
1601 TensorShape::IsValid(s.shape()) && s.has_value()) {
1602 Tensor begin(b.dtype(), b.shape());
1603 if (!begin.FromProto(b.value())) {
1604 return errors::InvalidArgument("Cannot parse tensor from proto: ",
1605 b.value().DebugString());
1606 }
1607 Tensor size(s.dtype(), s.shape());
1608 if (!size.FromProto(s.value())) {
1609 return errors::InvalidArgument("Cannot parse tensor from proto: ",
1610 s.value().DebugString());
1611 }
1612 // The node is replaceable iff unknown_rank == false &&
1613 // begin == 0 && (size == -1 || size == input_shape) for all dimensions
1614 bool replaceable = !input.shape().unknown_rank();
1615 for (int j = 0; replaceable && j < input.shape().dim_size(); ++j) {
1616 if (begin.dtype() == DT_INT32) {
1617 replaceable &= begin.vec<int>()(j) == 0;
1618 } else {
1619 replaceable &= begin.vec<int64>()(j) == 0;
1620 }
1621 if (size.dtype() == DT_INT32) {
1622 replaceable &= (size.vec<int>()(j) == -1 ||
1623 size.vec<int>()(j) == input.shape().dim(j).size());
1624 } else {
1625 replaceable &=
1626 (size.vec<int64>()(j) == -1 ||
1627 size.vec<int64>()(j) == input.shape().dim(j).size());
1628 }
1629 }
1630 if (replaceable) {
1631 ReplaceOperationWithIdentity(0, node, optimized_graph);
1632 continue;
1633 }
1634 }
1635 }
1636
1637 if (use_shape_info && IsTile(*node) &&
1638 properties->GetInputProperties(node->name()).size() == 2) {
1639 const auto& m = properties->GetInputProperties(node->name())[1];
1640 if (TensorShape::IsValid(m.shape()) && m.has_value()) {
1641 Tensor multiplies(m.dtype(), m.shape());
1642 if (!multiplies.FromProto(m.value())) {
1643 return errors::InvalidArgument("Cannot parse tensor from proto: ",
1644 m.value().DebugString());
1645 }
1646 // The node is replaceable iff all values in multiplies are 1.
1647 bool replaceable = true;
1648 if (multiplies.dtype() == DT_INT32) {
1649 for (int j = 0; replaceable && j < multiplies.vec<int>().size();
1650 ++j) {
1651 replaceable &= multiplies.vec<int>()(j) == 1;
1652 }
1653 } else {
1654 for (int j = 0; replaceable && j < multiplies.vec<int64>().size();
1655 ++j) {
1656 replaceable &= multiplies.vec<int64>()(j) == 1;
1657 }
1658 }
1659 if (replaceable) {
1660 ReplaceOperationWithIdentity(0, node, optimized_graph);
1661 continue;
1662 }
1663 }
1664 }
1665
1666 if (use_shape_info && IsPad(*node) &&
1667 properties->GetInputProperties(node->name()).size() >= 2) {
1668 const auto& p = properties->GetInputProperties(node->name())[1];
1669 if (TensorShape::IsValid(p.shape()) && p.has_value()) {
1670 Tensor paddings(p.dtype(), p.shape());
1671 if (!paddings.FromProto(p.value())) {
1672 return errors::InvalidArgument("Cannot parse tensor from proto: ",
1673 p.value().DebugString());
1674 }
1675 // The node is replaceable iff all values in paddings are 0.
1676 bool replaceable = true;
1677 // The operation requires it to be int32 value so we don't check for
1678 // 1nt64.
1679 const auto flatten = paddings.flat<int32>();
1680 for (int j = 0; replaceable && j < flatten.size(); ++j) {
1681 replaceable &= flatten(j) == 0;
1682 }
1683 if (replaceable) {
1684 ReplaceOperationWithIdentity(0, node, optimized_graph);
1685 continue;
1686 }
1687 }
1688 }
1689
1690 if (use_shape_info && IsSqueeze(*node) &&
1691 !properties->GetInputProperties(node->name()).empty()) {
1692 // https://www.tensorflow.org/api_docs/python/tf/squeeze mentions it's
1693 // error to squeeze a dimension that is not 1, so we only need to check
1694 // whether the input has > 1 size for each dimension.
1695 const auto& shape =
1696 properties->GetInputProperties(node->name())[0].shape();
1697 // The node is replaceable iff
1698 // unknown_rank == false && (dim_size == 0 || all dims have size > 1)
1699 bool replaceable = !shape.unknown_rank();
1700 for (int j = 0; replaceable && j < shape.dim_size(); ++j) {
1701 replaceable &= shape.dim(j).size() > 1;
1702 }
1703 if (replaceable) {
1704 ReplaceOperationWithIdentity(0, node, optimized_graph);
1705 continue;
1706 }
1707 }
1708
1709 if (IsPack(*node) && NumNonControlInputs(*node) == 1 &&
1710 !OptimizedNodeExists(*node, "_const_axis")) {
1711 // Create constant axis node.
1712 Tensor axis_t(DT_INT32, TensorShape({}));
1713 NodeDef* axis_node = optimized_graph->add_node();
1714 axis_node->set_name(OptimizedNodeName(*node, "_const_axis"));
1715 const int axis = node->attr().at("axis").i();
1716 if (!SetTensorValue(DT_INT32, axis, &axis_t).ok() ||
1717 !CreateNodeDef(axis_node->name(), TensorValue(&axis_t), axis_node)
1718 .ok()) {
1719 continue;
1720 }
1721 // Add a control dependency to make sure axis_node is in the right frame.
1722 const string ctrl_dep = ConstantFolding::AddControlDependency(
1723 node->input(0), graph_, node_map_.get());
1724 axis_node->add_input(ctrl_dep);
1725 axis_node->set_device(node->device());
1726 node->set_op("ExpandDims");
1727 if (node->attr().count("axis") != 0) {
1728 node->mutable_attr()->erase("axis");
1729 }
1730 if (node->attr().count("N") != 0) {
1731 node->mutable_attr()->erase("N");
1732 }
1733 (*node->mutable_attr())["Tdim"].set_type(DT_INT32);
1734 node->add_input(axis_node->name());
1735 if (node->input_size() > 2) {
1736 node->mutable_input()->SwapElements(1, node->input_size() - 1);
1737 }
1738 graph_modified_ = true;
1739 continue;
1740 }
1741
1742 // Move constants past Enter.
1743 if (IsEnter(*node) && node->input_size() > 0) {
1744 if (node->attr().count("is_constant") == 0 ||
1745 !node->attr().at("is_constant").b()) {
1746 continue;
1747 }
1748 const string& node_name = node->name();
1749 const NodeDef* input = node_map_->GetNode(node->input(0));
1750 if (input != nullptr && IsReallyConstant(*input) &&
1751 !OptimizedNodeExists(*input, "_enter")) {
1752 auto fanouts = node_map_->GetOutputs(node_name);
1753 // Find non-constant nodes that consume the output of *node.
1754 std::vector<NodeDef*> consumers;
1755 for (NodeDef* fanout : fanouts) {
1756 if (!IsConstant(*fanout)) {
1757 for (int i = 0; i < fanout->input_size(); ++i) {
1758 if (fanout->input(i) == node_name) {
1759 consumers.push_back(fanout);
1760 break;
1761 }
1762 }
1763 }
1764 }
1765 if (!consumers.empty()) {
1766 NodeDef* new_node = optimized_graph->add_node();
1767 *new_node = *input;
1768 new_node->set_name(OptimizedNodeName(*input, "_enter"));
1769 new_node->set_device(node->device());
1770 new_node->clear_input();
1771 new_node->add_input(AsControlDependency(node_name));
1772 node_map_->AddNode(new_node->name(), new_node);
1773 node_map_->AddOutput(node_name, new_node->name());
1774 for (NodeDef* consumer : consumers) {
1775 for (int i = 0; i < consumer->input_size(); ++i) {
1776 if (NodeName(consumer->input(i)) == node_name) {
1777 node_map_->UpdateInput(consumer->name(), node_name,
1778 new_node->name());
1779 consumer->set_input(i, new_node->name());
1780 }
1781 }
1782 }
1783 graph_modified_ = true;
1784 continue;
1785 }
1786 }
1787 }
1788
1789 // Switch(x, x) will always feed false to its false branch and true to
1790 // its true branch. By rewriting the graph a bit, we can propagate these
1791 // constants down the two output branches, and just use control dependencies
1792 // to trigger the selected one at runtime. For example,
1793 //
1794 // +------+
1795 // x-->|Switch|-->a (in practice there may be multiple consumers of each
1796 // x-->| |-->b output branch.)
1797 // +------+
1798 //
1799 // Is rewritten as
1800 //
1801 // +------+
1802 // x-->|Switch|-->Identity--^>Const(false)-->a
1803 // x-->| |-->Identity--^>Const(true)-->b
1804 // +------+
1805 if (node->op() == "Switch" && node->input(0) == node->input(1) &&
1806 !OptimizedNodeExists(*node, "_const_false") &&
1807 !OptimizedNodeExists(*node, "_const_true")) {
1808 bool already_optimized = true;
1809 // If the optimization was already applied, the switch would have exactly
1810 // one Identity node consuming each of its outputs, each without any
1811 // non-control outputs.
1812 auto fanouts = node_map_->GetOutputs(node->name());
1813 if (fanouts.size() == 2) {
1814 for (NodeDef* fanout : fanouts) {
1815 if (!IsIdentity(*fanout) ||
1816 NumNonControlOutputs(*fanout, *node_map_) > 0) {
1817 already_optimized = false;
1818 break;
1819 }
1820 }
1821 }
1822 Tensor false_t(DT_BOOL, TensorShape({}));
1823 Tensor true_t(DT_BOOL, TensorShape({}));
1824 // Make sure we don't proceed if this switch node was already optimized.
1825 if (!already_optimized && SetTensorValue(DT_BOOL, true, &true_t).ok() &&
1826 SetTensorValue(DT_BOOL, false, &false_t).ok()) {
1827 // Copy the set of consumers of the switch as they will be manipulated
1828 // below.
1829 const std::set<NodeDef*>& consumer_set =
1830 node_map_->GetOutputs(node->name());
1831 std::vector<NodeDef*> consumers(consumer_set.begin(),
1832 consumer_set.end());
1833 std::sort(consumers.begin(), consumers.end(),
1834 [](const NodeDef* n1, const NodeDef* n2) {
1835 return n1->name() < n2->name();
1836 });
1837 // Create constant false & true nodes.
1838 NodeDef* false_node = optimized_graph->add_node();
1839 false_node->set_name(OptimizedNodeName(*node, "_const_false"));
1840 if (!CreateNodeDef(false_node->name(), TensorValue(&false_t),
1841 false_node)
1842 .ok()) {
1843 continue;
1844 }
1845 false_node->set_device(node->device());
1846
1847 NodeDef* true_node = optimized_graph->add_node();
1848 true_node->set_name(OptimizedNodeName(*node, "_const_true"));
1849 if (!CreateNodeDef(true_node->name(), TensorValue(&true_t), true_node)
1850 .ok()) {
1851 continue;
1852 }
1853 true_node->set_device(node->device());
1854
1855 // Add controls from the switch ports to the constants, and connect the
1856 // constants to the original switch outputs.
1857 const string false_port = node->name();
1858 const string true_port = strings::StrCat(node->name(), ":1");
1859 const string false_ctrl_dep =
1860 AddControlDependency(false_port, optimized_graph, node_map_.get());
1861 false_node->add_input(false_ctrl_dep);
1862 const string true_ctrl_dep =
1863 AddControlDependency(true_port, optimized_graph, node_map_.get());
1864 true_node->add_input(true_ctrl_dep);
1865
1866 node_map_->AddNode(false_node->name(), false_node);
1867 node_map_->AddNode(true_node->name(), true_node);
1868 node_map_->AddOutput(NodeName(false_ctrl_dep), false_node->name());
1869 node_map_->AddOutput(NodeName(true_ctrl_dep), true_node->name());
1870
1871 for (NodeDef* consumer : consumers) {
1872 for (int i = 0; i < consumer->input_size(); ++i) {
1873 const string& input = consumer->input(i);
1874 if (input == false_port) {
1875 consumer->set_input(i, false_node->name());
1876 node_map_->UpdateInput(consumer->name(), false_port,
1877 false_node->name());
1878 } else if (input == true_port) {
1879 consumer->set_input(i, true_node->name());
1880 node_map_->UpdateInput(consumer->name(), true_port,
1881 true_node->name());
1882 }
1883 }
1884 }
1885 graph_modified_ = true;
1886 continue;
1887 }
1888 }
1889 if (IsSimplifiableReduction(*node)) {
1890 // Replace the reduction node with an identity node, that can be further
1891 // optimized by the model pruner.
1892 DataType output_type;
1893 if (node->attr().count("T") > 0) {
1894 output_type = node->attr().at("T").type();
1895 } else {
1896 // This is an 'any' or 'all' reduction. The output is always boolean.
1897 output_type = DT_BOOL;
1898 }
1899 node->set_op("Identity");
1900 node->clear_attr();
1901 (*node->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(output_type);
1902 *node->mutable_input(1) = AsControlDependency(node->input(1));
1903 graph_modified_ = true;
1904 continue;
1905 }
1906 if (use_shape_info && IsSimplifiableReshape(*node, *properties)) {
1907 DataType output_type = node->attr().at("T").type();
1908 node->set_op("Identity");
1909 node->clear_attr();
1910 (*node->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(output_type);
1911 *node->mutable_input(1) = AsControlDependency(node->input(1));
1912 graph_modified_ = true;
1913 continue;
1914 }
1915
1916 const bool is_mul = IsMul(*node);
1917 const bool is_matmul = IsMatMul(*node);
1918 const bool is_add = IsAdd(*node) || IsBiasAdd(*node);
1919 const bool is_sub = IsSub(*node);
1920 const bool is_any_div = IsAnyDiv(*node);
1921 // Simplify arithmetic operations with ones or zeros.
1922 if (use_shape_info &&
1923 (is_mul || is_matmul || is_add || is_sub || is_any_div) &&
1924 properties->HasInputProperties(node->name()) &&
1925 properties->HasOutputProperties(node->name())) {
1926 const NodeDef* x = node_map_->GetNode(node->input(0));
1927 const NodeDef* y = node_map_->GetNode(node->input(1));
1928 if (x == nullptr || y == nullptr) {
1929 return errors::InvalidArgument("Invalid inputs to node: ",
1930 node->DebugString());
1931 }
1932 const TensorShapeProto& output_shape =
1933 properties->GetOutputProperties(node->name())[0].shape();
1934
1935 // Simplify element-wise multiplication by ones or addition/subtraction
1936 // of zeros.
1937 const TensorShapeProto& y_shape =
1938 properties->GetInputProperties(node->name())[1].shape();
1939 const bool x_is_zero = IsZeros(*x);
1940 const bool x_is_one = x_is_zero ? false : IsOnes(*x);
1941 const bool y_matches_output_shape = ShapesEqual(output_shape, y_shape);
1942 if (y_matches_output_shape &&
1943 ((is_mul && x_is_one) || (is_add && x_is_zero))) {
1944 // 1 * y = y or 0 + y = y.
1945 ReplaceOperationWithSnapshot(1, node, optimized_graph);
1946 continue;
1947 }
1948
1949 if (y_matches_output_shape && (is_sub && x_is_zero)) {
1950 // Replace 0 - y with Neg(y).
1951 ReplaceSubtractionFromZeroByNegation(node, optimized_graph);
1952 continue;
1953 }
1954
1955 // Replace 1 / y with Reciprocal op.
1956 if (y_matches_output_shape && is_any_div && x_is_one) {
1957 DataType type = node->attr().at("T").type();
1958 if (DataTypeIsFloating(type) || DataTypeIsComplex(type)) {
1959 ReplaceDivisionOfOnesByReciprocal(node, optimized_graph);
1960 continue;
1961 }
1962 }
1963
1964 const TensorShapeProto& x_shape =
1965 properties->GetInputProperties(node->name())[0].shape();
1966 const bool y_is_zero = IsZeros(*y);
1967 const bool y_is_one = y_is_zero ? false : IsOnes(*y);
1968 const bool x_matches_output_shape = ShapesEqual(output_shape, x_shape);
1969 if (x_matches_output_shape && (((is_mul || is_any_div) && y_is_one) ||
1970 ((is_add || is_sub) && y_is_zero))) {
1971 // x * 1 = x or x / 1 = x or x +/- 0 = x
1972 ReplaceOperationWithSnapshot(0, node, optimized_graph);
1973 continue;
1974 }
1975
1976 // Simplify multiplication and matmul by zeros.
1977 // Also optimize zeros divided by a tensor, but only if we are in
1978 // aggressive mode, since we might get rid of divisions by zero.
1979 bool optimize_zeros_divided_by_y =
1980 is_any_div && x_is_zero && is_aggressive;
1981 if ((x_is_zero || y_is_zero) &&
1982 (is_mul || is_matmul || optimize_zeros_divided_by_y)) {
1983 const PartialTensorShape shp(output_shape);
1984 if (shp.IsFullyDefined()) {
1985 AttrValue dtype_attr;
1986 if (node->op() == "SparseMatMul") {
1987 dtype_attr.set_type(DT_FLOAT);
1988 } else {
1989 dtype_attr = node->attr().at("T");
1990 }
1991 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(ReplaceOperationWithConstant(
1992 0, dtype_attr, output_shape, node, optimized_graph));
1993 continue;
1994 }
1995 // Even if an input shape is only partially known, we may known that it
1996 // matches the output shape and thus forward the corresponding zero
1997 // input.
1998 if ((is_mul || is_any_div) && x_is_zero && x_matches_output_shape) {
1999 ReplaceOperationWithIdentity(0, node, optimized_graph);
2000 continue;
2001 } else if (is_mul && y_is_zero && y_matches_output_shape) {
2002 ReplaceOperationWithIdentity(1, node, optimized_graph);
2003 continue;
2004 }
2005 }
2006 }
2007
2008 // Strength reduce floating point division by a constant Div(x, const) to
2009 // multiplication by the reciprocal Mul(x, Reciprocal(const)). This in turn
2010 // will be constant folded to Mul(x, 1.0/const).
2011 if (node->input_size() >= 2 && (IsRealDiv(*node) || IsDiv(*node))) {
2012 const string& const_input = node->input(1);
2013 const NodeDef* denom = node_map_->GetNode(const_input);
2014 CHECK(denom != nullptr);
2015 if (!IsReallyConstant(*denom)) {
2016 continue;
2017 }
2018 if (node->attr().count("T") == 0) {
2019 continue;
2020 }
2021 DataType type = node->attr().at("T").type();
2022 if (IsDiv(*node) &&
2023 !(DataTypeIsFloating(type) || DataTypeIsComplex(type))) {
2024 continue;
2025 }
2026 // Insert new reciprocal op and change node from Div to Mul.
2027 NodeDef* reciprocal_node = optimized_graph->add_node();
2028 reciprocal_node->set_name(OptimizedNodeName(*node, "_recip"));
2029 reciprocal_node->set_op("Reciprocal");
2030 reciprocal_node->set_device(node->device());
2031 node->set_op("Mul");
2032 // Re-wire inputs and outputs.
2033 reciprocal_node->add_input(const_input);
2034 (*reciprocal_node->mutable_attr())["T"].set_type(type);
2035 node->set_input(1, reciprocal_node->name());
2036 node_map_->AddNode(reciprocal_node->name(), reciprocal_node);
2037 node_map_->UpdateOutput(node->name(), const_input,
2038 reciprocal_node->name());
2039 graph_modified_ = true;
2040 continue;
2041 }
2042
2043 // Consider the transformation
2044 //
2045 // + + = parent
2046 // / \ / \
2047 // C + -- > X + = children
2048 // / \ / \
2049 // X Y C Y = leaves
2050 //
2051 // where C is constant and X is non-constant, and '+' denotes an
2052 // associative and commutative operator like addition or multiplication.
2053 // This optimization pushes constants down in the tree to canonicalize it.
2054 // Moreoever, in cases where the child node has a second constant input Y
2055 // we will create a leaf node that can be folded, e.g.
2056 //
2057 // Add(C1, Add(C2, X)) -> Add(X, Add(C1, C2)) -> Add(X, C1 + C2)
2058 //
2059 // TODO(rmlarsen): Handle non-associative/non-commutative operators like
2060 // subtraction and division, as well as mixed subtraction/addition,
2061 // division/multiplication.
2062 // Don't touch BiasAdd since they can't handle vectors as their first
2063 // inputs.
2064 if (has_fetch_ && (IsAdd(*node) || is_mul) &&
2065 NumNonControlInputs(*node) == 2) {
2066 NodeDef* left_child = node_map_->GetNode(node->input(0));
2067 NodeDef* right_child = node_map_->GetNode(node->input(1));
2068 // One child must be constant, and the other the same op as the parent.
2069 if (node->op() != left_child->op() && node->op() != right_child->op()) {
2070 continue;
2071 }
2072 const bool left_child_is_constant = IsReallyConstant(*left_child);
2073 const bool right_child_is_constant = IsReallyConstant(*right_child);
2074 if (!left_child_is_constant && !right_child_is_constant) {
2075 continue;
2076 }
2077 if (node->device() != left_child->device() ||
2078 node->device() != right_child->device()) {
2079 continue;
2080 }
2081 NodeDef* op_child_node =
2082 left_child_is_constant ? right_child : left_child;
2083 NodeDef* const_child_node =
2084 left_child_is_constant ? left_child : right_child;
2085 // Make sure that it is safe to change the value of the child node->
2086 if (op_child_node->input_size() < 2 ||
2087 NumNonControlOutputs(*op_child_node, *node_map_) > 1 ||
2088 nodes_to_preserve_.find(op_child_node->name()) !=
2089 nodes_to_preserve_.end()) {
2090 continue;
2091 }
2092
2093 // Identify the nodes to swap.
2094 NodeDef* left_leaf = node_map_->GetNode(op_child_node->input(0));
2095 NodeDef* right_leaf = node_map_->GetNode(op_child_node->input(1));
2096 const bool left_leaf_is_constant = IsReallyConstant(*left_leaf);
2097 const bool right_leaf_is_constant = IsReallyConstant(*right_leaf);
2098 if (left_leaf_is_constant && right_leaf_is_constant) {
2099 // Child is already foldable, leave it alone.
2100 continue;
2101 }
2102 const int non_const_leaf_input = left_leaf_is_constant ? 1 : 0;
2103 const int parent_const_input = left_child_is_constant ? 0 : 1;
2104 const auto& child_output = node_map_->GetOutputs(op_child_node->name());
2105 if (child_output.find(const_child_node) != child_output.end()) {
2106 // If there is a control edge from the child op to C, the transformation
2107 // would create a cycle in the graph. We know that it must be a control
2108 // edge. We can replace such a control edge with a control edge from A
2109 // to C.
2110 CHECK(MaybeRemoveControlInput(op_child_node->name(), const_child_node,
2111 graph_, node_map_.get()));
2112 NodeDef* other_leaf = left_leaf_is_constant ? left_leaf : right_leaf;
2113 MaybeAddControlInput(other_leaf->name(), const_child_node, graph_,
2114 node_map_.get());
2115 }
2116
2117 // Swap the constant child with a non-constant leaf node.
2118 node_map_->UpdateInput(node->name(), node->input(parent_const_input),
2119 op_child_node->input(non_const_leaf_input));
2120 node_map_->UpdateInput(op_child_node->name(),
2121 op_child_node->input(non_const_leaf_input),
2122 node->input(parent_const_input));
2123 std::swap(*node->mutable_input(parent_const_input),
2124 *op_child_node->mutable_input(non_const_leaf_input));
2125 graph_modified_ = true;
2126 continue;
2127 }
2128
2129 // Partial constant propagation through IdentityN.
2130 if (IsIdentityN(*node) && NumNonControlInputs(*node) > 0) {
2131 const std::set<NodeDef*>& tmp = node_map_->GetOutputs(node->name());
2132 const std::vector<NodeDef*> consumers(tmp.begin(), tmp.end());
2133 bool updated_graph = false;
2134 for (int input_idx = 0; input_idx < node->input_size(); ++input_idx) {
2135 const string& input = node->input(input_idx);
2136 if (IsControlInput(input)) {
2137 break;
2138 }
2139 const NodeDef* input_node = node_map_->GetNode(NodeName(input));
2140 if (input_node == nullptr) {
2141 LOG(ERROR) << "Bad input: " << input;
2142 break;
2143 }
2144 // Forward constant inputs to outputs and add a control dependency on
2145 // the IdentityN node.
2146 if (IsReallyConstant(*input_node)) {
2147 // Update each consumer.
2148 for (NodeDef* consumer : consumers) {
2149 bool add_dep = false;
2150 for (int consumer_input_idx = 0;
2151 consumer_input_idx < consumer->input_size();
2152 ++consumer_input_idx) {
2153 const string& consumer_input =
2154 consumer->input(consumer_input_idx);
2155 if (IsControlInput(consumer_input)) {
2156 break;
2157 }
2158 int output_idx;
2159 const string input_node_name =
2160 ParseNodeName(consumer_input, &output_idx);
2161 if (input_node_name == node->name() && output_idx == input_idx) {
2162 consumer->set_input(consumer_input_idx, input);
2163 // We will keep the input from IdentityN through a control
2164 // dependency, so we only need to add the consumer as an output
2165 // for the constant input node.
2166 node_map_->AddOutput(NodeName(input), consumer->name());
2167 add_dep = true;
2168 }
2169 }
2170 if (add_dep) {
2171 consumer->add_input(AsControlDependency(node->name()));
2172 updated_graph = true;
2173 }
2174 }
2175 }
2176 }
2177
2178 if (updated_graph) {
2179 for (NodeDef* consumer : consumers) {
2180 DedupControlInputs(consumer);
2181 }
2182 graph_modified_ = true;
2183 continue;
2184 }
2185 }
2186
2187 // Partial constant folding for associative operators:
2188 // Split AddN/AccumulateNV2 to enable partial
2189 // folding of ops when more than one but not all inputs are constant.
2190 // For AddN and AccumulateNV2, we may furthermore reorder inputs, since
2191 // addition is commutative.
2192 const int num_non_control_inputs = NumNonControlInputs(*node);
2193 if (IsAggregate(*node) && IsCommutative(*node) &&
2194 num_non_control_inputs > 2) {
2195 const int num_control_inputs =
2196 node->input_size() - num_non_control_inputs;
2197 std::vector<int> const_inputs;
2198 std::vector<int> nonconst_inputs;
2199 for (int i = 0; i < node->input_size(); ++i) {
2200 const string& input = node->input(i);
2201 const NodeDef* input_node = node_map_->GetNode(NodeName(input));
2202 CHECK(input_node != nullptr) << input;
2203 if (!IsControlInput(input) && IsReallyConstant(*input_node)) {
2204 const_inputs.push_back(i);
2205 } else {
2206 // Non-const and control inputs.
2207 nonconst_inputs.push_back(i);
2208 }
2209 }
2210 // Promote AccumulateNV2 with all constant inputs to AddN, since it is
2211 // a fake node that cannot be constant folded by itself.
2212 if (const_inputs.size() == num_non_control_inputs &&
2213 node->op() == "AccumulateNV2") {
2214 node->set_op("AddN");
2215 node->mutable_attr()->erase("shape");
2216 graph_modified_ = true;
2217 continue;
2218 }
2219 const string new_node_name = OptimizedNodeName(
2220 *node, strings::StrCat("_partial_split_", const_inputs.size()));
2221 if (1 < const_inputs.size() &&
2222 const_inputs.size() < num_non_control_inputs &&
2223 !node_map_->NodeExists(new_node_name)) {
2224 NodeDef* added_node = optimized_graph->add_node();
2225 *added_node = *node;
2226 // Always use AddN for the constant node, since AccumulateNV2 is a fake
2227 // node that cannot be constant folded, since it does not have a kernel.
2228 added_node->set_op("AddN");
2229 added_node->mutable_attr()->erase("shape");
2230 added_node->set_name(new_node_name);
2231 node_map_->AddNode(added_node->name(), added_node);
2232 added_node->clear_input();
2233 for (int i : const_inputs) {
2234 added_node->add_input(node->input(i));
2235 node_map_->UpdateOutput(NodeName(node->input(i)), node->name(),
2236 added_node->name());
2237 }
2238
2239 // Overwrite the first const input with the added node.
2240 node->set_input(const_inputs[0], added_node->name());
2241 node_map_->AddOutput(added_node->name(), node->name());
2242 nonconst_inputs.push_back(const_inputs[0]);
2243 // Compact the remaining inputs to the original node.
2244 std::sort(nonconst_inputs.begin(), nonconst_inputs.end());
2245 int idx = 0;
2246 for (int i : nonconst_inputs) {
2247 if (idx != i) {
2248 node->set_input(idx, node->input(i));
2249 }
2250 ++idx;
2251 }
2252 node->mutable_input()->DeleteSubrange(nonconst_inputs.size(),
2253 const_inputs.size() - 1);
2254 (*node->mutable_attr())["N"].set_i(node->input_size() -
2255 num_control_inputs);
2256 properties->ClearInputProperties(node->name());
2257 (*added_node->mutable_attr())["N"].set_i(const_inputs.size());
2258 graph_modified_ = true;
2259 continue;
2260 }
2261 }
2262
2263 // Partial constant folding for Concat which is not commutative, so
2264 // we have to preserve order and can only push consecutive runs of constant
2265 // inputs into sub-nodes.
2266 if (IsConcat(*node) && num_non_control_inputs > 3 &&
2267 node->name().rfind("_partial_split_") == string::npos) {
2268 int axis_arg = -1;
2269 int begin = 0;
2270 int end = num_non_control_inputs;
2271 if (node->op() == "Concat") {
2272 begin = 1;
2273 axis_arg = 0;
2274 } else if (node->op() == "ConcatV2") {
2275 end = num_non_control_inputs - 1;
2276 axis_arg = num_non_control_inputs - 1;
2277 } else {
2278 continue;
2279 }
2280
2281 const NodeDef* axis_arg_node =
2282 node_map_->GetNode(NodeName(node->input(axis_arg)));
2283 if (axis_arg_node == nullptr || !IsReallyConstant(*axis_arg_node)) {
2284 // We cannot constant fold Concat unless we the axis argument is
2285 // constant. Skip node.
2286 continue;
2287 }
2288
2289 // We search for consecutive runs of constant inputs in the range
2290 // [begin:end[ and push then down into child nodes.
2291 std::vector<std::pair<int, int>> constant_input_runs;
2292 int first = begin;
2293 int last = begin;
2294 while (last < end) {
2295 while (first < end && !IsReallyConstant(*node_map_->GetNode(
2296 NodeName(node->input(first))))) {
2297 ++first;
2298 }
2299 // Invariant: node[first] is constant || first >= end.
2300 last = first + 1;
2301 while (last < end && IsReallyConstant(*node_map_->GetNode(
2302 NodeName(node->input(last))))) {
2303 ++last;
2304 }
2305 // Invariant: node[last] is not constant || last >= end
2306 // Discard intervals shorter than 2 elements.
2307 if (first < end && (last - first) > 1) {
2308 constant_input_runs.emplace_back(first, last);
2309 }
2310 first = last;
2311 }
2312
2313 // Skip if all inputs are constant, and let constant folding take over.
2314 if (constant_input_runs.size() == 1 &&
2315 constant_input_runs[0].first == begin &&
2316 constant_input_runs[0].second == end) {
2317 continue;
2318 }
2319 std::set<int> inputs_to_delete;
2320 for (auto interval : constant_input_runs) {
2321 // Push the constant inputs in the interval to a child node than can be
2322 // constant folded.
2323 const string new_node_name = OptimizedNodeName(
2324 *node, strings::StrCat("_partial_split_", interval.first));
2325 if (node_map_->NodeExists(new_node_name)) {
2326 break;
2327 }
2328 NodeDef* added_node = optimized_graph->add_node();
2329 *added_node = *node;
2330 added_node->set_name(new_node_name);
2331 node_map_->AddNode(added_node->name(), added_node);
2332 added_node->clear_input();
2333 for (int i = interval.first; i < interval.second; ++i) {
2334 added_node->add_input(node->input(i));
2335 node_map_->UpdateOutput(NodeName(node->input(i)), node->name(),
2336 added_node->name());
2337 if (i != interval.first) {
2338 inputs_to_delete.insert(i);
2339 }
2340 }
2341 added_node->add_input(node->input(axis_arg));
2342 (*added_node->mutable_attr())["N"].set_i(interval.second -
2343 interval.first);
2344 node_map_->AddOutput(NodeName(node->input(axis_arg)),
2345 added_node->name());
2346
2347 // Overwrite the first constant input with the result of the added
2348 // child node.
2349 node->set_input(interval.first, added_node->name());
2350 node_map_->AddOutput(added_node->name(), node->name());
2351 }
2352 if (!constant_input_runs.empty()) {
2353 graph_modified_ = true;
2354 if (!inputs_to_delete.empty()) {
2355 // Fix up the inputs to the original node.
2356 std::vector<string> tmp(node->input().begin(), node->input().end());
2357 node->clear_input();
2358 for (int i = 0; i < tmp.size(); ++i) {
2359 if (inputs_to_delete.find(i) == inputs_to_delete.end()) {
2360 node->add_input(tmp[i]);
2361 }
2362 }
2363 (*node->mutable_attr())["N"].set_i(node->input_size() - 1);
2364 properties->ClearInputProperties(node->name());
2365 }
2366 continue;
2367 }
2368 }
2369 }
2370
2371 return Status::OK();
2372}
2373
2374Status ConstantFolding::RunOptimizationPass(Cluster* cluster,
2375 const GrapplerItem& item,
2376 GraphDef* optimized_graph) {
2377 node_map_.reset(new NodeMap(graph_));
2378 nodes_whitelist_.clear();
2379 // Fold fetch nodes iff it has a single fanout. Note that if a fetch node
2380 // has a single fanout, it would be rewritten as a constant with the same
2381 // node name, and therefore users are still able to fetch it. This is not
2382 // the case if the node has multiple fanouts, and constant folding would
2383 // replace the node with multiple constants (each for one fanout) with
2384 // new names, and as a result users would not be able to fetch the node any
2385 // more with the original node name.
2386 for (const auto& fetch : item.fetch) {
2387 const NodeDef* fetch_node = node_map_->GetNode(fetch);
2388 if (fetch_node && NumOutputs(*fetch_node, graph_) == 1) {
2389 nodes_whitelist_.insert(fetch_node->name());
2390 }
2391 }
2392
2393 GraphProperties properties(item);
2394 // It's possible to feed a placeholder with a tensor of any shape: make sure
2395 // that the shape inference deals with this conservatively unless we're in
2396 // aggressive mode.
2397 const bool assume_valid_feeds = opt_level_ == RewriterConfig::AGGRESSIVE;
2398 Status s = properties.InferStatically(assume_valid_feeds);
2399 const bool can_use_shape_info = s.ok();
2400
2401 if (can_use_shape_info) {
2402 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(MaterializeShapes(properties));
2403 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(MaterializeConstants(properties));
2404 }
2405 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(FoldGraph(optimized_graph));
2406 node_map_.reset(new NodeMap(optimized_graph));
2407 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
2408 SimplifyGraph(optimized_graph, &properties, can_use_shape_info));
2409
2410 return Status::OK();
2411}
2412
2413Status ConstantFolding::Optimize(Cluster* cluster, const GrapplerItem& item,
2414 GraphDef* optimized_graph) {
2415 // TensorFlow flushes denormals to zero and rounds to nearest, so we do
2416 // the same here.
2417 port::ScopedFlushDenormal flush;
2418 port::ScopedSetRound round(FE_TONEAREST);
2419 nodes_to_preserve_ = item.NodesToPreserve();
2420 for (const auto& feed : item.feed) {
2421 feed_nodes_.insert(NodeName(feed.first));
2422 }
2423
2424 if (cpu_device_ == nullptr) {
2425 owned_device_.reset(new DeviceSimple());
2426 cpu_device_ = owned_device_.get();
2427 }
2428
2429 has_fetch_ = !item.fetch.empty();
2430 GrapplerItem item_to_optimize = item;
2431 *optimized_graph = item.graph;
2432 int64 node_count;
2433 do {
2434 graph_modified_ = false;
2435 item_to_optimize.graph.Swap(optimized_graph);
2436 graph_ = &item_to_optimize.graph;
2437 *optimized_graph = GraphDef();
2438 node_count = graph_->node_size();
2439 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
2440 RunOptimizationPass(cluster, item_to_optimize, optimized_graph));
2441 } while (graph_modified_ || optimized_graph->node_size() != node_count);
2442 *optimized_graph->mutable_library() = item.graph.library();
2443 *optimized_graph->mutable_versions() = item.graph.versions();
2444
2445 return Status::OK();
